A quarry worker in Embu on Tuesday evening died after he accidentally blew himself with explosives he was using to blast stones. Joseph Ndwiga died on the spot. He was looking for building stones to sell to his customers. Witnesses said he drilled a hole in the quarry and put in some explosives at 7pm. Fellow quarry workers said after putting in the explosives in the hole Ndwiga did not move away and he stood nearby. They said after a short time, the force from the explosives threw Ndwiga in the air and stones rained on him. Fellow workers rushed to save him but it was too late. Witnesses said police from Itabua police station are investigating. The body was removed to the Embu Level Five Teaching and Referral Hospital mortuary.      